replies.bodyText:
See https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/ZOOKEEPER-2342. The comments suggest that is basically just works, and the only reason they've stuck with v1 so far is simply for compatibility with v1 configuration syntax. Also:
$ grep -Fr 'import org.apache.log' .
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/Log4jAuditLoggerTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Layout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/Log4jAuditLoggerTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Level;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/Log4jAuditLoggerTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Logger;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/Log4jAuditLoggerTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.SimpleLayout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/Log4jAuditLoggerTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.WriterAppender;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/StandaloneServerAuditTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Layout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/StandaloneServerAuditTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Level;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/StandaloneServerAuditTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Logger;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/StandaloneServerAuditTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.SimpleLayout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/audit/StandaloneServerAuditTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.WriterAppender;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/test/ReadOnlyModeTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Layout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/test/ReadOnlyModeTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Level;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/test/ReadOnlyModeTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Logger;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/test/ReadOnlyModeTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.WriterAppender;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/server/quorum/QuorumPeerMainTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Level;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/server/quorum/QuorumPeerMainTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.Logger;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/server/quorum/QuorumPeerMainTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.PatternLayout;
./zookeeper-server/src/test/java/org/apache/zookeeper/server/quorum/QuorumPeerMainTest.java:import org.apache.log4j.WriterAppender;

I.e. the only place where they depend on log4j v1 is in the tests.
For CC that grep shows nothing.
So there's pretty much nothing to do, unless you want to get bogged down in the config compatibility debate. But that needn't concern us: In both cases we could switch really easily if we wanted to, it's just a matter of writing a log4j2 config file or using v2's support for reading v1 configs: http://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/manual/migration.html and arranging the classpath appropriately.
